{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2861-library-new-request-javax.servlet-jsp-api-2.0-bb57fb87\n\nThe most likely failing stage is generated test quality / dynamic-access coverage, not the final Gradle test execution. The run metrics ended with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and dynamic-access coverage remained `0/2 (0.00%)`. In the generated test project, `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/Jsp_apiTest.java` is still a scaffold placeholder, and `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still reports both reflection call sites as uncovered: `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`.\n\nThere was also an intermediate compile failure in `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T11-14-59-223471Z.log` where `:compileTestJava` failed in `TagSupportTest.java` because `containsExactlyInAnyOrder(...)` could not accept the inferred generic type. However, later reruns in `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T11-19-49-929150Z.log` and `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T11-23-42-548280Z.log` show `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` for both `:nativeTest` and `:test`, so the remaining blocker appears to be insufficient/scaffolded tests and unresolved coverage rather than an unrepaired build break.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T11-03-17-647951Z.log`\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T11-14-59-199602Z.log`\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T11-14-59-223471Z.log`\n- `logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T11-23-42-548280Z.log`\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Replace the scaffold `Jsp_apiTest` with library-specific tests that intentionally exercise the `class$` / `Class.forName` paths in `SimpleTagSupport` and `TagSupport`.\n2. Re-run the single-library test flow and confirm `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` rises above the 50% gate.\n3. If those call sites still cannot be credited by the coverage tooling, document that limitation and adjust the test/coverage strategy before opening a PR."}}
